{"article_id":"GiHEYVsAO3A9oTeM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republican Senators Susan Collins of Maine , Mitt Romney of Utah , Lisa Murkowski of Alaska and Lamar Alexander of Tennessee are getting attention","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"as an important step in President Donald Trump ' s impeachment trial nears .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"The Senate looks set to vote next week on whether to subpoena new witnesses or documents ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"with that action slated to come","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"after Trump ' s lawyers and House managers finish their opening arguments","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"- as well as after senators get up to 16 hours","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"to ask questions .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"There could be a 51-49 vote in favor of calling witnesses","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"if the four GOP lawmakers back that approach","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"and all 47 senators","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"who caucus with the Democrats","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"also support it .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Here ' s what the four Republican senators ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"often viewed as moderates ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"have said so far on the issue :","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Sen. Susan Collins ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"who is in a closely watched re-election race ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"said the following in a statement Tuesday :","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"\" As I said last week ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"while I need to hear the case argued and the questions answered ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"I anticipate","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"that I would conclude","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"that having additional information would be helpful .","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"It is likely that I would support a motion","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to subpoena witnesses at that point in the trial ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"just as I did in 1999 .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"\" ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"who is in a closely watched re-election race ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"said the following in a statement Tuesday :","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"\" As I said last week ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"while I need to hear the case argued and the questions answered ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"I anticipate","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"that I would conclude","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"that having additional information would be helpful .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"It is likely that I would support a motion","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"to subpoena witnesses at that point in the trial ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"just as I did in 1999. \"","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Sen. Mitt Romney ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"who has criticized Trump in the past ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"had this to say on Jan. 13 :","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"\" I ' ve said","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"I ' d like to hear from John Bolton .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"I expect","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"that ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"barring some kind of surprise ,","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"I ' ll be voting in favor","depth":16},{"id":46,"text":"of hearing from witnesses after those opening arguments . \" ,","depth":16},{"id":47,"text":"who has criticized Trump in the past ,","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"had this to say on Jan. 13 :","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"\" I ' ve said","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"I ' d like to hear from John Bolton .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"I expect","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"barring some kind of surprise ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"I ' ll be voting in favor","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"of hearing from witnesses after those opening arguments. \"","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski has been cagey on the issue .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"According to an Alaska Public Media report ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"she told reporters in Anchorage on Jan. 18","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"that , while at the trial ' s start she would be voting with her party against amendments","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"demanding witnesses ,","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"no one should assume","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"she will oppose calling witnesses later .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"has been cagey on the issue .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"According to an Alaska Public Media report ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"she told reporters in Anchorage on Jan. 18","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"that ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"while at the trial ' s start she would be voting with her party against amendments","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"demanding witnesses ,","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"no one should assume","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"she will oppose calling witnesses later .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Sen. Lamar Alexander ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"who plans to retire","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"after his current term ends this year ,","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"has been coy in recent interviews","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and said","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"\" maybe \" he will vote for witnesses","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"but \" maybe not , \"","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"according to a Politico report on Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"He is unlikely to be the 51st vote for witnesses ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"but rather ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"if he ' s feeling the need for witnesses ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"other Republicans would join him","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"and scramble plans","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"on how to handle new testimony in the trial ,","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"the report added .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Beyond these four lawmakers , Sens . Rob Portman of Ohio , Cory Gardner of Colorado and Martha McSally of Arizona are also among the Republicans","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"talked about at various times in recent weeks as possible swing voters in the impeachment trial ,","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"though McSally lashed out at a CNN reporter","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"who asked for her view on the calling of new witnesses ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"labeling him a \" liberal hack \"","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"and then promoting the testy exchange on her Twitter account and on a campaign-fundraiser T-shirt .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Related :","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"GOP senators reportedly told","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"their heads ' will be on a pike '","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"if they vote against Trump","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"Even if the Senate votes for witnesses and documents ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"that ' s widely expected","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"only to prolong the trial ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"rather than lead to Trump ' s ouster .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"That helps explain why the stock market DJIA , +0.40 % SPX , +0.34 % hasn ' t reacted much to impeachment-related developments .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"The stakes around the impeachment process are \" low for markets , high for senators , \"","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"said Charles Gabriel of Capital Alpha Partners in a recent note .","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"Related :","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Why investors are so calm about impeachment","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"- and what it would take for that to change","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"And see :","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"For the stock market , impeachment is just a sideshow","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"A two-thirds majority of the Senate","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"- or 67 senators -","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"must vote","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"to convict the president","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"to remove him from office .","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"And even on the issue of witnesses , two Republican senators","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"who spoke to the Hill on condition of anonymity","depth":8},{"i